# Mobile-First Responsive

Most CoachingHunt users are on **mobile**. Design and implement for small screens first, then enhance for tablet and desktop.

## Build order

1. Layout and content must work at **320px–390px** width before adding `sm:` / `md:` / `lg:` breakpoints.
2. Default Tailwind classes = mobile. Use `md:` and up only to add columns, show sidebars, or widen containers.
3. Test mentally (or in browser) at mobile width for every UI change.

## Layout patterns

```jsx
// ✅ Mobile stack → desktop grid
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">

// ✅ Full-width mobile, constrained desktop
<div className="mx-auto w-full max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6">

// ✅ Sticky bottom CTA on mobile for key actions (book demo, submit)
<div className="fixed bottom-0 inset-x-0 border-t bg-white p-4 md:static md:border-0 md:p-0">
```

- **Dashboards**: sidebar stacks above content on mobile (`w-full md:w-64`), not hidden without a mobile nav alternative.
- **Tables**: convert to stacked cards on mobile, or enable horizontal scroll with a visible hint — never clip content silently.
- **Filters**: collapsible drawer or accordion on mobile; inline on `md+`.

## Touch and readability

- Tap targets **≥ 44×44px** — use `py-3`, `min-h-11`, adequate gap between links/buttons.
- Primary actions: full-width on mobile (`w-full md:w-auto`).
- Body text ≥ `text-sm`; avoid tiny labels. Line length readable without horizontal scroll.
- Forms: one column, large inputs (`Input` defaults), numeric keyboards via `type="tel"` / `type="email"` where appropriate.

## Navigation

- Every link reachable on mobile — no desktop-only nav without a hamburger/menu or bottom bar.
- Keep header compact; prioritize search and "Book demo" / "Find coachings" over secondary links.

## Performance on mobile

- Prefer server-rendered content; avoid heavy client bundles for listing pages.
- Use `Skeleton` placeholders sized for mobile card layout.
- Optimize images (appropriate sizes, lazy load below fold).

## Avoid on mobile

- Hover-only interactions (no `:hover`-only affordances).
- Multi-column forms, wide data tables, tiny icon-only buttons without labels.
- Fixed elements that cover >15% of viewport unless essential (sticky book CTA is OK).
